0080c0: 1a01 ae00                              |001a: const-string v1, "Chess for Android was written by Aart J.C. Bik.

Use the touch screen, trackball, or keyboard to make a move. Press the MENU button for more options, such as changing playing strength. Long-press anywhere in the notation window to export the game as PGN or FEN to the clipboard, or save and load the game as a file.

The application complies with the official chess rules, including en-passant, castling, and minor promotion. It recognizes a draw by stalemate, the fifty move rule, threefold repetition, and insufficient material.

The GUI supports the UCI and XBoard protocols. Please consult the developer's website for details on importing third party engines.

Thanks to Elisabeth Bik and Jyrki Alakuijala for designing chess piece sets.
